rdf:Description.lla:note: Note in the Official Log, states that on 1867-05-07 at 4.30 pm, John E. Evans was 'found very drunk and disorderley and making noise about the deck'. The Master states hat he tried to get 'him below and to go to bed at 6', but when he (the Master) later went 'below to take tea John E. Evans came into the cabin and lay hold of the tea kettle and struck me on my head and the water being hot and cut my head badly'. The Master goes onto say that the crewman 'commenced to brake the cabin and all the earthen ware'. A boat was ordered ashore to fetch the police ' for he was dangerous on board'.
Notes in the Official Log, states that Richard Cummings was drunk on one occasion, and attempted to desert the ship on another. He was sentenced to 1 month in prison.
